THE WORKED PLANNED FOR THIS PROJECT WOULD INCLUDE THE REMOVAL OF THE 2 OLD OVERSIZED 2100HP GAS/#6 TAMPELLA BOILERS, AND REPLACE THEM WITH 3 APPROPRIATELY SIZED 750HP CLEAVER BROOKS DRY BACK FIRETUBE GAS/#2 BOILERS (TWO TO RUN UNDER NORMAL OPERATING CONDITIONS, AND ONE FOR BACK UP). BY SWITCHING OVER TO THESE HIGHER EFFICIENCY BOILERS WILL REMOVE OUR DEPENANCY ON #6 FUEL OIL, WHICH THE DEPARTMENT'S WAIVER IS EXPIRING IN APRIL OF THIS YEAR.  OUR FAILURE TO BE ABLE TO SWITCH OVER TO OILWHEN NATIONAL GRID REQUIRES US WILL RESULT IN A MORE EXPENSIVE THERM RATE AND POSSIBLE FINES. HAVING THE NEW BOILERS ON #2 OIL IS A DRASTICSTEP IN CLEANING THE CITY'S AIR OF CO2 EMISSIONS.
